<h2 id="generating-the-constructor">Generating the Constructor <a class="headerlink" href="service-shortcuts#generating-the-constructor" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Now in <code>QuoteGenerator</code>, let's pretend like we need access to some service - like
maybe we want to log something inside of here. The normal way of doing that is with
dependency injection, where we pass the logger through via the <code>constructor</code>. So let's
do exactly that, but with as little work as possible.</p>
<p>I could type <code>public function __construct</code>, but instead I'm going to use the generate
command. Hit <code>command+n</code> and pick the "Constructor" option from the menu here. I don't
think this constructor comment is all that helpful, so go back into preferences with
<code>command+,</code>, search for "templates", and under "file and code templates", we have
one called "PHP Constructors". I'll just go in here and delete the comment from the
template.</p>
<p>Ok, let's try adding the constructor again. Much cleaner:</p>
